<div id="review_1857689287" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1857689287" />
    <a title="N.N. Light" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23234551-n-n-light"><img alt="N.N. Light" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1629639172p2/23234551.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1857689287?book_show_action=true">Dec 07, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="N.N. Light" class="user" itemprop="url" name="N.N. Light" href="/user/show/23234551-n-n-light">N.N. Light</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23234551-n-n-light?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23234551-n-n-light?shelf=reviews-by-mr-n">reviews-by-mr-n</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1857689287" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9951358922434660319">Amazingly I had never ever heard of this Grisham work until I read the book. I have seen many a book made into a movie and never really liked any of those. I have read other Grisham works and never liked those. I loved this book. <br/><br/>The most amazing part of this book is that it is written from the perspective of a 7 year old. This so reminds me of the fantastic &apos;A Christmas Story&apos; which is told from the point of view of little Ralphie. Here Luke tells the story and it is one that grips the reader. </span>
  <span id="freeText9951358922434660319" style="display:none">Amazingly I had never ever heard of this Grisham work until I read the book. I have seen many a book made into a movie and never really liked any of those. I have read other Grisham works and never liked those. I loved this book. <br /><br />The most amazing part of this book is that it is written from the perspective of a 7 year old. This so reminds me of the fantastic 'A Christmas Story' which is told from the point of view of little Ralphie. Here Luke tells the story and it is one that grips the reader. His perspective on both the Mexicans, the Hill People, his family, his neighbors and the townsfolk is enlightening. <br /><br />The story is simple yet expansive and really takes a person back to rural Arkansas in the 50s. From the troubles that come from Cotton farming to racial issues and poverty issues along with dreams of a better life this book is amazing. I can't recommend this high enough. The best work of Grisham in my view and this book stays on my bookshelf.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9951358922434660319" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


